content:
Remove-AzureADUserExtension

Removes a user extension.

Syntax

Remove-AzureADUserExtension -ExtensionName <String> -ObjectId <String> [<CommonParameters>]
Remove-AzureADUserExtension -ExtensionNames <System.Collections.Generic.List`1[System.String]>
 -ObjectId <String> [<CommonParameters>]

Description

The Remove-AzureADUserExtension cmdlet removes a user extension from Azure Active Directory (AD).

Parameters

-ExtensionName

Specifies the name of an extension.

Type:String
Required:True
Position:Named
Default value:None
Accept pipeline input:True (ByPropertyName, ByValue)
Accept wildcard characters:False
-ExtensionNames

Specifies an array of extension names.

Type:System.Collections.Generic.List`1[System.String]
Required:True
Position:Named
Default value:None
Accept pipeline input:True (ByPropertyName, ByValue)
Accept wildcard characters:False
-ObjectId

Specifies an object ID.

Type:String
Required:True
Position:Named
Default value:None
Accept pipeline input:True (ByPropertyName, ByValue)
Accept wildcard characters:False

Related Links

  • Get-AzureADUserExtension
  • Set-AzureADUserExtension
